headline: Evaluating T-Mobile US (TMUS) Valuation After Recent Share Price Weakness
summary: Recent share performance and business scale T-Mobile US (TMUS) has seen its share price slip about 9% over the past month and 11% over the past 3 months, while the one year total return is roughly 19% lower. In contrast to that market performance, the company currently reports annual revenue of about US$85.8b and net income of roughly US$11.9b. headline: Verizon (VZ) Dividend Safety: 7% Yield From Telecom Giant – Too Good to Be True?
summary: Verizon Communications (NYSE:VZ) offers income investors a 6.9% yield, roughly double the S&P 500’s dividend return. The telecom giant has raised its dividend for 21 consecutive years, four years from Dividend King status. But the stock has underperformed the broader market in recent years.
